      "evidence": [
        "`runtime_ops.go` defines many operation structs (`RuntimeContainerOps`, `RuntimeUrbitOps`, `RuntimeStartupOps`, `RuntimeWireguardOps`, `RuntimeNetdataOps`, `RuntimeMinioOps`, etc.) plus seam registry and default constructors in one place.",
        "The same file also performs environment wiring (`network.NewNetworkRuntime`, config/click/startram function binding), while other runtime services such as `WiFiRuntimeService` in `wifi_runtime_api.go` independently implement separate runtime wrapper composition patterns."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Split orchestration runtime seams by concern (container/urbit/startup/network/security), and introduce a shared runtime-construction pattern used across modules so service runtime APIs are structured consistently.",
